reviews.text: Th only place in Tsuen Wan you can enjoy a 1970 Hong Kong style restaurant. Place is dimly lit and everything seemed old fashioned but they are good. Any plate with steak/pork will be enough for a regular meal, adding rice or spaghetti would be a waste of food.

In Hong Kong, restaurant can survive More than 10 years, It's kind of a miracle. This is one of the old restaurant left in HK which more than 30yrs. I won't said quality steakhouse, it's more like childhood memories of Hong Kong people. If you would like to know what HK steakhouse looks like in 80's. This is the right place.
